source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hearty-turkey-burger-noodle-soup-662001c7b4db7806c6d9f956
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(peeled and diced into ½-inch pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, onion, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until onion is softened and beef is browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. (The beef will finish cooking in the next step.)

> Swap in turkey for beef.

Stir in @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz}, @beef stock concentrate{2}, @cavatappi pasta{6%oz}, 3 1/2 cups water, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} (6½ cups water and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

Increase heat to high, then cover and bring soup to a boil.

Once soup is boiling, uncover and cook, stirring occasionally, until pasta is al dente and beef is cooked through, ~{9-11%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

While soup cooks, roughly chop @parsley{1/4%oz}.

Divide soup between bowls. Garnish with parsley and serve.

> TIP: If you want to add a kick, stir in a pinch of chili flakes from your pantry!

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.